@node requirements "Requirements"

   Requirements of the @{"Simple" link Simple} version:

   - any Amiga with Kickstart 1.2+ will do.
   No external libraries are needed.



   Requirements of the @{"Complex" link Usage} version:

  - KickStart 2.04+
  - @{"Magic User Interface" link mui} 3.3+
  - Hard disk is highly recommended (MUI !!)

   To  make  it  more  readable,  setting  a  big font in the preferences
program is advisable.  The following fonts look especially good:

  @{fg fill}Amifont@{fg text} 24, @{fg fill}Compact@{fg text} 24, @{fg fill}Coop@{fg text} 24, @{fg fill}Franklin@{fg text} 23, @{fg fill}FuturaB@{fg text} 20, @{fg fill}FuturaX@{fg text} 24,
  @{fg fill}Gill@{fg text} 24, @{fg fill}Helvetica@{fg text} 24.
@endnode

@node Usage "How to use MagicDice"

    Click @{"here" link Simple} to learn about the Simple version.

  It's  really very simple and even Amiga beginners should be able to use
it without experiencing problems.
  After  starting  the  program  the  main  window  and defined MagicDice
windows  (if  you'd  already defined them) will appear.  Now activate the
Edit Mode gadget to enable window editor.

  To  define  a new window use the Add gadget.  You can edit window title
as  well  as  MUI window ID code, which should be unique to every window.
This will allow MUI to remember window size and position during Snapshot.
  Use  @{fg highlight}Lower@{fg text}  and  @{fg highlight}Upper@{fg text}  gadgets  to  set range of values to be randomly
generated.   You  can also select font to use in this window.  Note, that
it's only possible before the window is opened.
  Now you can open the window by selecting Open checkbox.

  Every  window  contains a @{fg highlight}Generate@{fg text} button, which generates a new random
number for this window.  There also exists a Generate All gadget, located
in main window, which will generate new numbers for all opened windows.

  I guess the rest is simple enough to left it undocumented.
@endnode

@node Simple "Simple version"

 After  launching  programm  seven  windows  will appear (without defined
positions  - all in left upper corner).  In each of them you may generate
values:  1-4, 1-6, 1-8, 1-10, 1-12, 1-20, 1-100 (One window = one range!)
To generate value, you have to click on CLOSE gadget.  Closing windows is
impossible (!?).
 Programm  was  written  2  hours  before  session, when I had A500.  The
releasing reason is that not even has KS2.04.

@endnode

